rComments: Labs are on Sundays. Teacher is strict. Students are treated like future-chefs-to-be, when this is supposed to be a nutrition class where we should learn how to prepare food for different communities. Instead, the class that was supposed to be 1h30 lasted 30-45 min. The course material that was taught had already been learned in a previous class.

This is a mandatory class for Nutrition and Sabine does her best to make it a living hell. Very unhelpful when asked questions; doesn't know what she's talking about. Her directions for projects were completely useless and unrelated. She is more concerned about her 'reputation' than she is about you actually learning anything.
